                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13154226/comment/16447439",
                    "id": "16447439",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kou",
                        "name": "kou",
                        "key": "kou",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=kou&avatarId=30762",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=kou&avatarId=30762",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=kou&avatarId=30762",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=kou&avatarId=30762"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Kouhei Sutou",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Asia/Tokyo"
                    },
                    "body": "There is already one use case.\r\n\r\nC GLib bindings use {{gboolean}} for boolean value. {{bool}} in C99 is 1byte. So we can use {{bool}} value for the current {{valid_bytes}}. But {{gboolean}} isn't 1byte. It uses {{int}} (*1) as the real type.\r\n\r\n(*1) https://developer.gnome.org/glib/stable/glib-Basic-Types.html#gboolean\r\n\r\nIf {{AppendValues}} accepts {{const int*}} for {{valid_bytes}}, we can remove type conversion ({{gboolean}} -> {{uint8_t}}) from C GLib bindings.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kou",
                        "name": "kou",
                        "key": "kou",
                        "avatarUrls": {
